If you're happy and you know it... clap your hands!
If you're happy and you know it... clap your hands!
If you're happy and you know it, and you really want to show it...
If you're happy and you know it........ clap your hands!


Do you hear that?

Silence.

Nobody is happy!

THE DAILY MUNDACITY

Today, like any other day, was mediocre at best. Well, actually, the temperature was down ... so I guess that counts for something? I had the opportunity to completely disect a printer around lunch. My employer's nice Brother HL-1440 laser printer had several problems that weren't really worth fixing. In a last chance effort (with credit card in hand, of course) I took the bastard apart and unplugged the communications cables from the controller to the part I thought had gone bad. No luck there! Unfortunately, I didn't have a schematic of the board layouts, and had little clue as to which wires I needed to keep, and which ones I could disconnect. In the end, I had to buy a new printer anyway.

Words of Wisdom: Be cautious of any laser printer under $300, and not manufactured by HP. It very well may suck. (I say this, because HP has a good track record for printers, and is considered the best manufacturer in the business by most)

-----
